If the player clicks log out while in the cave, they will ''not'' be logged out immediately. Instead, the wave following the current wave will be prevented from spawning, giving the player the opportunity to log out without loss of progress. Clicking the log out button a second time ''will'' log the player out immediately, but the current wave will have to be repeated.

It is generally recommended for the player to use [[Ranged]] for most of the run, as it allows the player to [[safespot]] monsters and attack them from a distance. At the highest levels and gear, using [[melee]] can be faster than Ranged, though the player is likely to take additional damage from melee attacks. Using [[Magic]] with [[Water Wave]] or [[Water Surge]] works well due to TzHaars' 40% weakness to water spells; however it is generally slower and more expensive than ranged. [[Blood spells]], [[Vengeance]], and [[Thralls]] can be used to support the other combat styles instead of using magic as primary damage.

It is '''strongly''' recommended for Ranged users to check their ammunition supply before beginning a Fight Cave run and enter with as much as they can. Completing the Fight Cave takes a significant amount of time (often well over an hour for lower-level players) and requires a considerable amount of ammunition and potions. 

==Suggested skills==
While the Fight Cave does not have any strict level requirements, it is recommended that the player have at least the levels recommended below for their chosen combat method. Completing the Fight Cave is possible with lower levels, but this is not recommended unless the player has prior experience.
