==Choosing your weapon==
===Ranged===
====[[File:Toxic blowpipe.png]] Toxic blowpipe====
Requiring 75 [[Ranged]], the [[toxic blowpipe]] is very effective against all enemies in the Fight Caves, up to and including [[TzTok-Jad]]. Despite being less accurate and having a lower max hit than crossbows, the overall damage output is much higher due to its [[attack speed]] of 2 [[tick]]s on rapid. In addition, [[venom]] adds extra damage on the higher levelled enemies. The special attack, ''Toxic siphon'', provides healing, making this the top choice for a single weapon to take for the entire run.

====[[File:Twisted bow.png]] Twisted bow====
The [[Twisted bow]] is extremely effective against [[Ket-Zek]]s and TzTok-Jad, but poor against everything else. It is helpful against high [[Magic defence]] monsters that may take longer with the toxic blowpipe. It is not recommended to use it as the only weapon for the entire run, but is extremely effective when paired with the toxic blowpipe.

====[[File:Rune crossbow.png]] [[File:Dragon crossbow.png]] [[File:Armadyl crossbow.png]] Crossbows====
The [[Rune crossbow]] is an early-game accessible Ranged weapon, requiring 61 [[Ranged]] to use, while the [[Dragon crossbow|dragon]] and [[Armadyl crossbow|Armadyl]] crossbows require 64 Ranged and 70 Ranged, respectively. They fire every 5 ticks on rapid, but deal a lot of damage accurately. An off-hand can also be taken for Defence, the [[crystal shield]] makes [[Tok-Xil]] much less threatening while [[Ket-Zek]]s are still alive, or for offence, the [[twisted buckler]] for maximum damage or [[book of law]] for Prayer and accuracy. The accessibility of the rune crossbow makes it the earliest viable weapon [[Ironman mode|Ironmen]] use for getting their first fire cape, but higher tiered crossbows permit the use of [[dragon bolt]]s for extra damage. Another option is the [[hunters' sunlight crossbow]], which fires faster and can surpass firepower of many bows with the downside of only being able to use [[sunlight antler bolts]] and [[moonlight antler bolts]].

====[[File:Eclipse_atlatl.png]] Eclipse atlatl====
The [[Eclipse atlatl]] is a versatile two-handed weapon which scales uniquely with melee strength and ranged accuracy. It is particularly well suited to those with higher Strength levels and lower Ranged levels, and provides consistent damage to all fight caves enemies, often surpassing the rune crossbow and magic shortbow, although rarely matching the toxic blowpipe. When worn with the full set, it also gives the chance to inflict [[burn]] for additional damage and access to the eclipse atlatl's special attack. However, the inability to wield a shield combined with the significant decrease in ranged defence with eclipse moon armour compared to dragonhide armour can make using the Eclipse atlatl harder to execute. The [[Hunter's spear]] scales in a similar manner off of Strength and Ranged, but is available much earlier and performs similarly to a magic shortbow or rune crossbow firing broad ammunition, assuming appropriate gear is worn, such as [[Mixed hide]] or the eclipse set.

====[[File:Karil's crossbow.png]] [[File:Magic shortbow (i).png]] [[File:Crystal bow.png]] [[File:Bow of faerdhinen.png]] Other weapons====
Other weapons can fill a similar role to the toxic blowpipe, but the run will be slower. [[Karil's crossbow]] requires 70 [[Ranged]] and will perform well against all enemies, especially with the [[amulet of the damned]]'s double-tap effect with [[Karil's equipment]]. The [[magic shortbow (i)]] has only a 50 Ranged requirement, and will be faster than crossbows against the weaker enemies, but will taper off against the high-defence Ket-Zeks and Jad. Consider using both it and a crossbow for more timely clears. A [[crystal bow]] requires 70 Ranged to use and will work against all enemies, but it may run out of charges before you finish. Finally, the [[bow of faerdhinen|Bow of Faerdhinen]] with [[crystal armour]] is superior to the toxic blowpipe for overall clear speed, but requires [[Song of the Elves]]. With the Fight Cave being a multi-combat zone, the [[Venator bow]] is also a viable option during the rounds prior to TzTok-Jad.

===Supplements===
==== [[File:Ancient staff.png]] Blood spells ====
[[Blood spells]] from the [[Ancient Magicks]] spellbook have a [[life leech]] effect, which heals the caster by 25% of the damage dealt. With at least 56 [[Magic]] and completion of [[Desert Treasure I]], players can bring the runes for [[Blood Rush]] or better for reliable, practically unlimited healing against safespottable enemies.

===Utility===
====[[File:Holy wrench.png]] Holy wrench or Ring of the Gods (i)====
By carrying a [[holy wrench]], [[Prayer potion]]s and [[super restore]]s may restore an extra Prayer point per dose. This comes at the cost of one inventory slot and is only beneficial to save money or to maximise Prayer restored, which is only possible if the number of doses available is greater than the total restoration of one potion.

====[[File:Ancient_mace.png]] Ancient mace====
By using the [[ancient mace]] special attack, players can restore prayer points equal to the damage dealt. At lower prayer levels and with slow completions, if used consistently, this can lead to greater prayer points restored per inventory slot than a prayer potion could've provided, making it an effective option for a first fire cape.

