While fighting Jad, players must keep [[Protect from Melee]] on, switching to [[Protect from Missiles]]/[[Protect from Magic]] depending on what he is using, before immediately switching back to Protect from Melee between each of Jad's attacks. This is because, unlike his magic and ranged attacks, his melee attack does not give the player any time to react; the player's melee protection prayer must already be activated in the event that he uses this attack, in order to avoid taking damage.
This can be skipped completely by using the noxious halberd from out of Jad's melee range.

A strategy used when meleeing is to use [[thralls]] in order to speed up the encounter. Another strategy used is casting the [[Vengeance]] spell to recoil some damage back to the NPC.

