Magic only=

Using Magic to complete the Fight Caves is a reliable and effective strategy; however, it's worth noting that completion times will usually be slower when compared to other set-ups, since they output damage faster than Magic. This is typically also more expensive than comparable ranged setups and offers less defence. However, wearing magic armour does increase the effectiveness of blood spells, which might make a magic only approach feel easier.

Due to the 40% water weakness of TzHaar, using the standard spellbook's [[Water Wave]] or [[Water Surge]] is very effective in the fight cave. Using powered staves or ancient spells is also possible, but won't benefit from this weakness, thus they should generally not be considered unless using strong weapons such as a [[Tumeken's shadow]], though it is possible with lower tier weapons too.

If using [[Void Knight equipment]], wearing the Void mage helm, [[Void knight top|robe top]], [[Void knight robe|skirt]], and [[Void knight gloves|hands]], yields a 45% bonus to Magic accuracy. It requires 42 Attack, Strength, Defence, Ranged, Magic, Hitpoints and 22 Prayer.

;Pros
*No inventory slots will be occupied by armour pieces.

;Cons
*It can be quite expensive and slightly slower than ranged setups.
*A decent shield might be required to help offset the low defensive stats of magical armour.

